<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hi all,</p> <p>I have a question about egpu&#39;s and how to use them:</p> <p>i have 3 gpu&#39;s</p> <ol> <li>intel</li> <li>nvidia</li> <li>a amd egpu</li> </ol> <p>&#x200B;</p> <pre><code>see xrandr --setprovideroutputsource radeon Intel 0000:00:02.0 VGA compatible controller: Intel Corporation TigerLake-LP GT2 [Iris Xe Graphics] (rev 01) DeviceName: VGA Subsystem: ASUSTeK Computer Inc. Device 13dc Kernel driver in use: i915 Kernel modules: i915 -- 0000:01:00.0 VGA compatible controller: NVIDIA Corporation GA107M [GeForce RTX 3050 Ti Mobile] (rev a1) DeviceName: Second VGA Subsystem: ASUSTeK Computer Inc. Device 13dc Kernel driver in use: nvidia Kernel modules: nouveau, nvidia_drm, nvidia -- 0000:06:00.0 VGA compatible controller: Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. [AMD/ATI] Navi 10 [Radeon RX 5600 OEM/5600 XT / 5700/5700 XT] (rev c1) Subsystem: Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. [AMD/ATI] Reference RX 5700 XT Kernel driver in use: amdgpu Kernel modules: amdgpu </code></pre> <p>if i start for excample minecraft with</p> <pre><code>prime-run minecraft-launcher </code></pre> <p>it runs minecraft on the nvidia gpu</p> <p>but how do i run minecraft on the egpu?</p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p>im using the hardened kernel and it works as a charm with nvidia,</p> <p>i just cant get anything run on the AMD gpu and i don&#39;t know where to search for next.</p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p>P.S.</p> <p>to make the nvidia gpu work on the hardened kernel i needed to use nvidia-dkms not nvidia.</p> <p>then change nano /etc/mkinitcpio.conf to early load the nvidia modules</p> <pre><code>nano /etc/mkinitcpio.conf </code></pre> <p>then use</p> <pre><code>mkinitcpio -P </code></pre> <p>create pacman hooks that mkinicpio after every nvidia update (i think) just to be sure</p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p>then change the kernel start parameters and add ibs=off because i have a intel processor</p> <pre><code>nano /etc/default/grub </code></pre> <p>generate the grub config.</p> <pre><code>grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg </code></pre> <p>i tried a lot of commands but without luck:</p> <pre><code>__NV_PRIME_RENDER_OFFLOAD=1 __GLX_VENDOR_LIBRARY_NAME=amdgpu minecraft-launcher </code></pre> <p>i changed amdgpu to everything amd related.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Pure_Pasifist"> /u/Pure_Pasifist </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wgyz0j/egpu_arch_wayland_nvidia_working_amd_not/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wgyz0j/egpu_arch_wayland_nvidia_working_amd_not/">[comments]</a></span>